      "content": "{\n  \"cwd\": \"/Users/sam.zhang/Documents/codex-supervisor\",\n  \"execution_layer_policy\": {\n    \"agentic_lead_policy\": {\n      \"min_subagents\": 0,\n      \"policy\": \"off\",\n      \"required_evidence_grade\": \"self_reported\",\n      \"required_roles\": [],\n      \"solo_exception_for_artifact_only_gates\": false\n    },\n    \"allowed_dynamic_workflow_task_classes\": [],\n    \"codex_supervises_final_artifact\": true,\n    \"dynamic_workflow_task_class\": null,\n    \"lead_execution_layer\": \"single_lead_worker\",\n    \"mode\": \"lead_direct\",\n    \"preview_required_gates\": [],\n    \"supervision_layer\": \"codex_plus_lead\"\n  },\n  \"expected_decisions\": [],\n  \"expected_objections\": [],\n  \"expected_specialists\": [],\n  \"gate\": \"outcome_review\",\n  \"instruction\": \"Supervisor-owned workflow gate: outcome_review.\\n\\nIntent:\\nMake the detached workflow job's terminal outcome durable in the SQLite ledger so reconnecting clients can poll the final result from the ledger even when result.json is missing. Scope: add terminal outcome fields/migration to dual_agent_workflow_jobs; write terminal status and outcome atomically; make poll_dual_agent_workflow_job read ledger first; keep writing and reading result.json as a legacy cache only when the ledger lacks an outcome; record a discrepancy event when cache and ledger differ, with ledger winning. Non-goals: S3b event sourcing, S1/S2/S5 transport changes, gate/reviewer semantic changes.\\n\\nReview this gate against the current source artifacts and return a typed dual_agent_outcome.\\nUse decisions/objections to say whether the gate should accept, revise, or deny.\",\n  \"lead_skill\": null,\n  \"outcome_validation_policy\": {\n    \"fidelity_failure\": \"abort_to_operator\",\n    \"malformed_outcome\": \"retry_once_with_corrective_packet\",\n    \"subprocess_failure\": \"abort_to_operator\",\n    \"timeout\": \"abort_to_operator\"\n  },\n  \"packet_schema_version\": \"dua